==Swedish==
===Noun===
'''blida ''-n, blidor'''''
*[[Wiktionary:Swedish pronunciation|Pronunciation]]: {{IPAchar|/ˈbliːˌda/}}
#(''archaic'') [[trebuchet]]
#:''Det krävdes ett stort antal '''blidor''' för att inta fästningen.''
#:"It took a great number of trebuchets to capture the fortress."

====Etymology====
Since Old Swedish ''blidha'', from Medieval Latin ''blida'' with the same meaning. Originally from Greek ''ballein'' "to throw".

